.DT
start_situation
Disk World creator help
start_situation

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
start_situation -  Starts a situation previously added to the room that is managed by this object.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void start_situation(mixed label,
int do_start_mess)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^label%^RESET%^ - string or number labelling the situation
%^BOLD%^do_start_mess%^RESET%^ - 0 to supress the start_mess string
       This is to fake it that a situation has been 
       going for a while when really you just loaded it.
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/basic/situation_changer.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

Starts a situation previously added to the room
that is managed by this object.
These situations can be invoked manually with 
start_situation or automatically via
automate_situation. 
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
add_situation, end_situation, automate_situation

.EP

